<p>
Pacioli's built-in matrix operations.

<p> 
Matrices in Pacioli are indexed by arbitrary sets. Given some index sets
<math>
  <mi>P</mi>
</math>
and
<math>
  <mi>Q</mi>
</math>,
a matrix is a map
<math>
  <mi>P</mi>
  <mo>&times;</mo>
  <mi>Q</mi>
  <mo>&rarr;</mo>
  <mi>&Ropf;</mi>
</math>.

<p>
Further information can be found on the <a href="https://pgriffel.github.io/pacioli/">
documentation pages</a>:
<ul>
  <li>The <a href="http://pgriffel.github.io/pacioli/matrices.html">matrix tutorial</a> explains matrices and types</li>
  <li>The <a href="https://pgriffel.github.io/pacioli/manual.html">manual</a> has more information on matrices and types</li>
</ul>
</p>